HEADWORD: Pigfish
<hw>Pig"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any one of several species of salt-water grunts; --
called also <altname>hogfish</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
sculpin. The name is also applied locally to several other
fishes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

